Author: Karl Barnes
Subject: Killer
Body: Love it.  Wrote similar script for my Linux box w/default 16 char limit to deal with site limits but with the option to specify length. This people, is a great way to deal w/psswds w/out going nuts. The ability to generate 4 different STRONG psswd's based on 1 identical string & even prioritize them based on algorithm! Great & THX!  FWIW; I think writing a little script or one-liner using these techniques is well worth it even if you stick w/the pro's tools for password generation & managment.

Author: Stanley Augustowicz
Subject: Interesting concept
Body: Where this app fails is that most sites have a limit on how many characters your password can be (length). Crypt algorithm would output fewer characters, but it is realatively easy to crack using brute force :/
